  <description><![CDATA[<p>Palazzo Pascal is a perfect little oasis, high in the hills above Ravello. The views from here are wonderful – the hotel’s surrounded by terraces with olive groves and vines and it has some of the best sea views in the area. There’ll be no doubt in your mind that you’re on the Amalfi Coast when you stay here. We love the traditional interiors of the hotel. They’ve paid attention to every detail and the painted ceramic tiles on the floor are produced by the owners own local ceramic business, a popular trade in this region of Italy. If you fancy taking back a few souvenirs, you can head to their shop in Ravello.</p>
<p>There’s only seven bedrooms here, which gives the hotel a great authentic feel. Get the know the other guests over breakfast, which is served on the terrace. Take your time to linger over your coffee and enjoy the sea views. There’s a small pool with loungers and a views of the steps that’ll get you to Ravello if you’re feeling energetic. The hotel itself is actually in Scala, a little village above Ravello. This means you’ll get to escape the crowds when you want to relax.</p>
<p>We can highly recommend the hotel’s restaurant, Gli Ulivi. Make sure you try the fresh seafood dishes! The whole menu is bursting with locally sourced ingredients. Some of the vegetables and herbs are even are grown on the hotel’s terraces. It’s about ten minutes’ walk to the nearest shops and restaurants in the village of Scala, and Ravello is a short bus ride away, as are all the rest of the Amalfi Coast towns.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 1 hour 20 mins by private car from Naples airport.</p>]]></description>
