  <facilityDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong><u>Pools &amp; Beaches</u></strong></p>
<p>The swimming pool is on the terrace, where you'll find comfortable sun loungers the look out over the spectacular view. </p>
<p>There's a few beaches to choose from nearby that can be reached by bus or you can take the steep trails down to them. <span>If you're up for a walk, take the downward trail from the Villa to Atrani. It takes about two hours, but there's a lovely fresh spring on route where you can cool off. At the end of the trail you'll find the unspoiled beach and little town of Atrani, where you can have a refreshing swim and a bite to eat. The beach has lots of loungers that you can pay locally to use for the day. There's a bus that will take you back up to Scala if you don't fancy the uphill hike.</span></p>
<p>You'll also find the spaggia di Ravello, just east of Atrani where there's a smaller <span>100 metre stretch of sand surrounded by the dramatic cliffs that Ravello is perched above coast or to the west is the main beach in Amalfi. </span></p>
<p><span style="text-decoration: underline;"><strong>Activities</strong></span></p>
<p><strong>“Nonna Maria” cooking class</strong> where you'll be introduced to authentic Italian cooking.</p>
<p><strong>Wine Experience </strong>where you'll discover the local DOC wines like <span>Tramonti, those of Ravello and the whites of Furore.</span> Under the guidance of an expert sommelier you'll learn about the different methods of production in the region, as you taste the authentic flavours of wine and food in the area. <span id="more-143"></span></p>
<p>These experiences are bookable locally or directly with the hotel, subject to availability. </p>
<p><strong>Amalfi Coast Walking Trails </strong>can be reached straight from Palazzo Pascal. The quiet countryside location means that you’ll find some of the fantastic walking trails of the Amalfi Coast right on your doorstep. Some of them will lead you down to the beaches on the coast and others up along the steep terraces, where you can take in the spectacular views. Note that some of the trails involve lots of steep paths and steps. Be sure to head out prepared with good walking shoes, water and check the weather before you leave. </p>
<p><strong><u>General Facilities </u></strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Rooftop terrace</li>
<li>24 hour reception</li>
<li>Daily housekeeping</li>
<li>Laundry facilities (payable locally)</li>
<li>Free cots for infants (0-2 years, on request)</li>
<li>Shops, restaurants and bars about 400 metres away in Scala</li>
</ul>]]></facilityDescription>
